                            <comment id="15537132" author="bvernon" created="Fri, 30 Sep 2016 21:31:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch attached.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Needs CI and review&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15537146" author="yukim" created="Fri, 30 Sep 2016 21:36:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As far as I know, only nodetool and debug-cql source cassandra-env.sh.&lt;br/&gt;
Other tools do not yet (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-8167&quot; title=&quot;sstablesplit tool can be made much faster with few JVM settings&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-8167&quot;&gt;CASSANDRA-8167&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15537152" author="JIRAUSER308715" created="Fri, 30 Sep 2016 21:38:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;All the tools use max heap size on purpose there.  nodetool should just save MAX_HEAP_SIZE and restore it, like it does for JVM_OPTS&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15537184" author="bvernon" created="Fri, 30 Sep 2016 21:53:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Good point, will change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15537208" author="bvernon" created="Fri, 30 Sep 2016 22:07:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Changes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Reduced patch to be only for nodetool&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Saved orginal MAX_HEAP_SIZE value and restored it after loading cassandra-env.sh&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="15605502" author="eduard.tudenhoefner" created="Tue, 25 Oct 2016 14:44:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch looks good IMO and it does what it&apos;s supposed to be doing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
